Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.22,1:04:13.42,English,,0,0,0,,Pompey and Crassus were both optimists.\N{\rChinese}波贝和克拉苏都是乐观派。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.06,1:04:17.38,English,,0,0,0,,They were supporters of Sulla.\N{\rChinese}他们是苏拉的支持者。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.58,1:04:21.70,English,,0,0,0,,Remember, Sulla is the one who crushed the populars.\N{\rChinese}记得，苏拉是那个把民粘打败的。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.60,1:04:26.28,English,,0,0,0,,So Pompey and Crassus were conservatives.\N{\rChinese}再来，波贝尔·波普里亚里？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.46,1:04:29.20,English,,0,0,0,,They were optimists. Caesar was a populier.\N{\rChinese}他们是乐观派。凯撒是民粘。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.84,1:04:34.28,English,,0,0,0,,So the alliance was secret.\N{\rChinese}所以，合并发了。”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.38,1:04:38.08,English,,0,0,0,,It was completely unexpected. And that's why they were able to accomplish so much.\N{\rChinese}完全意外的，正是这点让他们能完成这么多事。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.40,1:04:41.28,English,,0,0,0,,Because politically, they were at odds with each other.\N{\rChinese}因为在政治上，彼此相互相冲突。”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.02,1:04:44.70,English,,0,0,0,,The reason why they formed an alliance is\N{\rChinese}他们结盟的原因是基本上是机缘巧合。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.30,1:04:46.66,English,,0,0,0,,just basically expedience.\N{\rChinese}波普里亚里有个要点要通过塞内特里。”
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.42,1:04:50.52,English,,0,0,0,,Pompey had issues that he wanted to pass through the Senate.\N{\rChinese}他又能很久久的…
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.92,1:04:54.88,English,,0,0,0,,Crassus had issues that he wanted to pass through the Senate and Caesar as well.\N{\rChinese}克拉苏也想把事发到参议院去，跟着也有个…
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.10,1:05:00.14,English,,0,0,0,,So they decided it would be politically expedient to work together.\N{\rChinese}再把它们…………………
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.44,1:05:03.08,English,,0,0,0,,And that's the genius of Caesar, okay?\N{\rChinese}……………………
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.24,1:05:04.46,English,,0,0,0,,He's very charismatic.\N{\rChinese}他很有魅力。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.82,1:05:06.46,English,,0,0,0,,He's very manipulative. So\N{\rChinese}他很有变幻。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.46,1:05:10.18,English,,0,0,0,,he was able to form an alliance with people\N{\rChinese}他能通过…
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.18,1:05:11.92,English,,0,0,0,,who were technically his enemies, okay?\N{\rChinese}谁是他的技术敌人，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.18,1:05:13.76,English,,0,0,0,,Pompey and Crassus were his enemies.\N{\rChinese}庙帕姆·克拉苏是他的敌人。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.10,1:05:16.50,English,,0,0,0,,They were politically at odds with him.\N{\rChinese}他们在政治上与他相对立。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.62,1:05:20.50,English,,0,0,0,,But Caesar was able to put aside political differences\N{\rChinese}但可萨尔能把政治差异放在一边
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.50,1:05:24.52,English,,0,0,0,,and form an alliance for the sake of interest and expediency.\N{\rChinese}但可萨古尔...??
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.68,1:05:28.58,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? But obviously this would not last very long.\N{\rChinese}...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.92,1:05:32.22,English,,0,0,0,,Any more questions?\N{\rChinese}1116. 还有什么问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.10,1:05:40.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Okay.\N{\rChinese}1117.. 先后??
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.38,1:05:44.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay, so next class, we're gonna look at the world\N{\rChinese}1111?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.76,1:05:46.54,English,,0,0,0,,that Caesar created.\N{\rChinese}那可萨尔创建的...??
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.90,1:05:51.44,English,,0,0,0,,Because after he dies, the Republic falls.\N{\rChinese}...???
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.72,1:05:55.88,English,,0,0,0,,So we will look at what happens after he dies\N{\rChinese}...????
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.88,1:05:59.44,English,,0,0,0,,and look at the birth of the Roman Empire,\N{\rChinese}...
